German Chocolate Cake*
  Momofuku Milk Bar

Crack Coconut:
3 tbsp light brown sugar, tightly packed
2/3 c sugar
1 tbsp milk powder
1 tbsp corn powder
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/4 tsp vanilla
4 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
3 tbsp heavy cream
2 egg yolks
1 c sweetened coconut

In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with paddle attachment, add sugars, milk and corn powder, and salt. Mix; add vanilla and butter. Stream in butter and yolks. Pour into loaf pan and bake for 8-10 min in 325F oven. Remove from oven and dump into bowl. Add coconut a little at a time.

pecan crunch:
3/4 c pecans, chopped & roasted
splash of grapeseed oil
1 tbsp light brown sugar
1/2 tsp salt
3/4 c feuilletine

Grind pecans and oil in food processor. Pour pecan butter into a bowl, add sugar and salt and mix. Add feuilletine and combine.


Soak:
1/4 c milk
2 tbsp ovaltine

Layer:
chocolate cake, soak, crack, pecan, frosting, cake, soak, crack, pecan, cake, frosting, top with 1/4 c toasted coconut

Recipe did not include:
chocolate malt buttercream frosting
chocolate cake

Notes: Can sub rice crispy or corn flakes for feulletine
